---
import Layout from "../layouts/layout.astro";
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import cyberdeck from '../assets/cyberdeck.jpeg';
---
<Layout title="About">
  <h1>IT & Programming</h1>
  <div class="cd-container">
    <p>Here is a Cyberdeck I built with a Raspberry Pi 4 and an ipad 2 using a VNC Server. </p>
    <Image class="cyberdeck" alt="cyberdeck" src={cyberdeck}/>
  </div>
  <div class="p-container">
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://canvasocegueda.netlify.com/">[Self Canvas]</a> Canvas platform for self studiers using MIT, coursera, or edx.</li>
      <li><a href="https://climate-change-delta.vercel.app/">[Climate Change]</a> This is a website I made on Climate Change vs Global warming.</li>
      <li><a href="http://alexocegueda.pythonanywhere.com/">[Phobia Finder]</a> This is an API I created to have a comprehensive list of phobias.<br> Currently gets an organic 580+ visitor/calls a month.</li>
      <li><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1LmoD2WehfDDj8WVCT-yEowzP9rfuyvlJfYieWoMgMMU/copy">[Conaway Game of Life]</a> Game of Life implemented in Google Docs</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

</Layout>

<style>
  a {
  color: blue;

  }
  .cyberdeck {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    margin-left: 1rem;
  }
  .cd-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 2rem auto; 
    display: flex;
  }
  p {
    margin-left: 1rem;
    align-self: center;
  }
  .p-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 2rem auto;
    display: column;
  }
</style>
